code: import pandas as pd import numpy as np from sklearn.model_selection import GroupKFold from sklearn.metrics import matthews_corrcoef import xgboost as xgb # Load data train_labels = pd.read_csv("input/train_labels.csv") train_tracking = pd.read_csv("input/train_player_tracking.csv") test_tracking = pd.read_csv("input/test_player_tracking.csv") sample_sub = pd.read_csv("input/sample_submission.csv") # Process contact IDs with proper type conversion def process_contact_id(df): split = df["contact_id"].str.split("_", n=4, expand=True) df["game_play"] = split[0] + "_" + split[1] df["step"] = split[2].astype(int) df["player1"] = split[3].astype(int) df["player2"] = split[4].apply(lambda x: int(x) if x != "G" else x) return df train_labels = process_contact_id(train_labels) train_labels["is_ground"] = (train_labels["player2"] == "G").astype(int) # Feature merging with fixed data types def merge_features(labels_df, tracking_df): # Player1 features merged = labels_df.merge( tracking_df.add_suffix("_1"), how="left", left_on=["game_play", "step", "player1"], right_on=["game_play_1", "step_1", "nfl_player_id_1"], ) # Player2 features for non-ground merged_pp = merged[merged["is_ground"] == 0].copy() merged_pp = merged_pp.merge( tracking_df.add_suffix("_2"), how="left", left_on=["game_play", "step", "player2"], right_on=["game_play_2", "step_2", "nfl_player_id_2"], ) # Ground contact features merged_g = merged[merged["is_ground"] == 1].copy() # Feature engineering merged_pp["distance"] = np.sqrt( (merged_pp["x_position_1"] - merged_pp["x_position_2"]) ** 2 + (merged_pp["y_position_1"] - merged_pp["y_position_2"]) ** 2 ) merged_pp["speed_diff"] = merged_pp["speed_1"] - merged_pp["speed_2"] merged_pp["accel_diff"] = merged_pp["acceleration_1"] - merged_pp["acceleration_2"] merged_g["speed"] = merged_g["speed_1"] merged_g["accel"] = merged_g["acceleration_1"] merged_g["orientation"] = merged_g["orientation_1"] features_g = merged_g[["speed", "accel", "orientation"]] features_g.columns = ["distance", "speed_diff", "accel_diff"] return pd.concat( [merged_pp[["distance", "speed_diff", "accel_diff"]], features_g] ), pd.concat([merged_pp["contact"], merged_g["contact"]]) X, y = merge_features(train_labels, train_tracking) # Temporal validation games = train_labels["game_play"].unique() train_games = games[: int(len(games) * 0.8)] val_mask = train_labels["game_play"].isin(train_games) X_train, X_val = X[val_mask], X[~val_mask] y_train, y_val = y[val_mask], y[~val_mask] # Model training model = xgb.XGBClassifier( objective="binary:logistic", n_estimators=1000, learning_rate=0.1, max_depth=7, subsample=0.8, colsample_bytree=0.8, eval_metric="logloss", ) model.fit( X_train, y_train, eval_set=[(X_val, y_val)], early_stopping_rounds=20, verbose=False ) # Validation metric val_pred = model.predict(X_val) print(f"Validation MCC: {matthews_corrcoef(y_val, val_pred):.4f}") # Generate submission test_df = process_contact_id(sample_sub) test_df["is_ground"] = (test_df["player2"] == "G").astype(int) X_test, _ = merge_features(test_df, test_tracking) test_df["contact"] = model.predict(X_test) test_df[["contact_id", "contact"]].to_csv("submission/submission.csv", index=False)
